# Dumpboard — project context

Internal exercise for the design team. Everyone builds a personal editable page (“blank canvas”) and publishes it on GitHub Pages in `people/<nick>/`. The shared hub collects feed items in one Pinterest-style feed.

**Language:** all user-facing copy and GitHub docs are **English only**.

## Files (deliverables)

- `canvas-editor.html` — single-file WYSIWYG editor (Canva-like). Designers download and open this.
- `index.html` — entry router: first visit → `start.html`, return visits → `hub.html` (`localStorage` `dumpboard_intro_seen`).
- `start.html` — intro / landing; “Let's start” sets the flag and goes to `hub.html`.
- `hub.html` — team feed.
- `people.json` — list of people `{ "nick", "folder": "people/<nick>" }` (auto-generated by Actions).
- `people/` — participant pages (one subfolder per person).
- `.github/workflows/generate-people.yml` — scans `people/<nick>/` and overwrites `people.json` on each push.
- `.claude/server.js`, `.claude/launch.json` — static Node server for local tests (NOT part of the product).

## Hard constraints (do NOT break)

- Everything in a single HTML file (inline style + script). No frameworks, no build step, no dependencies **except Google Fonts**.
- Editor works from disk (`file://`). Hub uses `fetch`, so HTTP only (GitHub Pages / local server), NOT `file://`.
- No backend, database. Editor state lives in page memory. `localStorage` only for `dumpboard_intro_seen` on the landing router.
- Editor network use: font loading only. Export must be self-contained/offline (except embedded YouTube).
- Code should stay readable and commented in **English**.

## Editor — architecture

- In-memory state: `state = { bg, items: [] }` (item order = z-index), plus `profile = { name, avatar }`.
- Element types: `text` (double-click to edit, 30 Google Fonts, color, bold), `image` (base64, auto-downscaled to 1600px JPEG 0.85), `sticker` (emoji/image), `youtube` (embedded player; editor shows `img.youtube.com/vi/<id>/hqdefault.jpg` + play).
- Canvas: **free full window** (NOT a fixed artboard). Positions in px.
- Interactions: drag, corner resize (image/youtube keep aspect ratio; text/sticker scale font), rotate, delete, smart guides.
- Undo/redo: JSON snapshot stack (`pushUndo()` before each change). Snapshots serialize `{bg, items}` (profile separate).
- Fonts: `<link>` from Google while editing. On font **selection**, woff2 → base64 in `fontCache` for offline export.
- `beforeunload` warns when there is unsaved work.

## Export (“Download my page”)

Always creates a **ZIP** (pure JS store method, custom CRC-32). Contains:

- `index.html` — clean page (no editor UI). Inline text, base64 images, YouTube as `<iframe>`. Embedded `@font-face` (base64) for **used** fonts only.
- `project.json` — full editable state for re-opening in the editor (Shift+click logo).
- `profile.json` (+ `avatar.jpg`) — if profile set.
- `feed.json` + `feed-images/*.jpg` — when the page has images or YouTube videos (auto-included in feed).

### Published page layout

- Export computes bounding box of all elements (with rotation), shifts to 0,0 (`offX/offY`, `PAD=24`), creates `.stage` in `#wrap`.
- Script scales `.stage` to `#wrap` width (max 900px, centered) — NOT full viewport width.
- Model: fill width + vertical scroll.

## Feed and hub

- `feed.json`: `{ generated, items: [...] }`. Image entry = `{ file, caption, added }`; video = `{ type:"youtube", videoId, caption, added }`. **No author field** — folder name is identity.
- Hub reads `people.json` → `people/<nick>/feed.json` (+ optional `profile.json`). Skips empty feeds silently. Missing image → placeholder.
- Feed video = **clickable thumbnail + play, opens YouTube in new tab** (no `<iframe>` on hub).
- `people.json` auto-generated by GitHub Actions. Participants upload only to `people/`, not repo root.

## Visual conventions

- Accent `#7c5cff`, warm bg `#fff7ed`, ink `#1f1d2b`. UI fonts: Inter + Space Grotesk. Editor ↔ hub consistency.

## Local testing

- Server: `node .claude/server.js` (port 8753). Hub: `http://localhost:8753/hub.html`, landing: `http://localhost:8753/start.html`.
- SVG needs content-type `image/svg+xml` in server.js.

## Common pitfalls

- After every change, **re-export and overwrite** files in the folder — old `index.html` does not update itself. Hard-refresh after upload (`Ctrl+Shift+R`).
- Embedded YouTube needs internet when viewing — only non-offline element.
- Editor positions are in window px; export normalizes and scales them.
